item.title: The Humble Home Page
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Hello there wayward travellers and I would like to welcome you all to my personal profile page where you can learn all about my journeys from the real world and the journeys and intricate Learning of my travels through the Interwebs to bring what I hope will have fun, adventure, joy and maybe even some emotion and heartfelt in the mix. But enough Dilly Dally, let's get exploring shall we.

On this website you will find

Exquisite bit and pieces of work from my past from the journey that I have been on for a good while and what they mean to me or what they represent

...or some other stuff like:

Learning about some of my intricate Hobbies and Interests from movies and Games to what I hope they lead me to do and create in the Future and some hopeful sneak peeks and ideas to share with you all

and even some stuff like:

Trying to make it into a portfolio where I may share a lot of my own work but I want to make this site something that we can all be a part of together from inspiration, to peace and comfort to the likes of spreading positivity to you when I can (I hope so anyway and that Is is not being annoying in any way like I feel I do a lot of times)

But anyways I hope that you take some time and have a look around and I hope by the end of it that I gave you a sense of peace (and If I haven't and made you annoyed then I am sorry for doing so). Take Care on your travels.

item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Our website address is: http://localhost/wordpress.

What personal data we collect and why we collect it

Comments

When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Contact forms

Cookies

If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Analytics

Who we share your data with

How long we retain your data

If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where we send your data

Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

Your contact information

Additional information

How we protect your data

What data breach procedures we have in place

What third parties we receive data from

What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data

Industry regulatory disclosure requirements

item.title: A few Introductions to your host of this evening
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Oh, Hello there wayward Internet Traveller, let me formally welcome you to this little site on this side of the cyberspace. I bet you are wondering who I am and what I do, well fret not as I am here to tell you all the important things about yours truly. I go by many names but to give a clear name I go by the name of Sam Harrison. I am a 20 year old that has the look of someone much older and a back pain that has me in the age of retirement at this point. I come from the strange and far off mythical place known as Ireland and it is quite a peaceful place to live. Anyway that is enough to discuss on who I am now for the important information: what am I interested in?

Well, we all have our own different interests and things we very much enjoy and for me that Is anything to do with Media. Ever since I was a small child, I have always been fascinated with the likes of Media like Movies, Tv, Music and Games and I think from that young age I have wanted to go into the world of all things to do with Media. Thankfully that career has been with me to this very day as I am currently finding myself in a college course doing a wide variety of areas in media from the likes of Film making and editing, Photography, Design, Website Development, Game Design and so much more and what I bring to it is my own weird and special charm to anything that I make and hope that with these skills I can soon make my way out into the big bad and scary world around me and get to leave my mark on the industry for the better.

When I am not making and crafting any big media thing and I have the free time to relax from working on college stuff or from working in my job (I work in the wonderous company of CEX selling all things entertainment) I do delve into watching Movies (some of my favourite Genres being Comedy, Action/Adventure and Animation (I have a soft spot for this genre)) I play some Video Games (Story Driven games all the way for me) Listening to music (Especially the Music of Comedy bands like NSP and TWRP or the likes of classic 80s and 90s music), Reading a lot of books, Drawing and Sketching, Meditation and Sleeping.

Anyway that is all that I want to talk about right now but this wont be the only Blog that I will do, I will return in the Near Future with all things and topics from the likes of a new report, some hot tea gossip and so much more so I hope to see you again.

Farewell Wayward Cyberspace Traveller

Sam Harrison

item.title: Something Sketchy this way comes
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Hello again. This is another little section of these intricate blogs that I would like to call Sams Sketchbook Street where I will share some of my elaborate and detailed or even dumb quick sketches that I do in my endless Little Sketchbook of mine that I will share now and again. This first edition of Sketchbook Street is one of my more recent sketches that I have done which is a character sketch based on a character from a beautifully animated music video known as Starlight Brigade

A good portion of this creation was basing it from the music video snippet and then slowly sketching it from the outer part first and then building it out to the detail of the cape, sleeve of his clothing, his Ear and from the detailing of his facial features and his flowing hair and it was over the process of about an hour or so and I think it turned out really well.

Well that Is all I have to show on this edition of Sketchbook Street. Join me next time for more fun little drawings and doodles.

Farewell and safe travels

Sam Harrison

item.title: Things seem grim and Scary Let this Music calm you
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Well Hello once again to all of you wayward Cyberspace Travellers and welcome to another one of my tales of Blog. My, my dear traveller you look tired and restless and you seem to be quite worried of all the stuff that is going on outside in the scary place known as the real world. I too myself have been caught in the fear and scaring aspects of the world and it can be hard to escape it but I do have something that will hopefully help you out with your nerves, calm you, bring a bit of joy and also a bit of groove to your step.

Provided to you here is a nice little tune of encouragement and Grooviness in a song called Somewhere Out There from the intergalactic Canadian Band known as TWRP. These sound and music that they produce have helped me many a times on my own travels and tasks and I hope it helps you too. Take a while and relax and when you are ready to continue on your journey to the cyberspace that you will something to help.

Until next time, farewell and safe travels

Sam Harrison

item.title: The Hopeful Good News show
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Hello there wayward traveller and I would like to welcome you to another tales and adventures from the wayward Traveller myself. Now today I would like to test out and try out a pilot for something I like to call the Good News Network where I will try and look through the likes of the current day news programme and talk about the sense of finding the good in those stories. So today I will talk about the likes of three big thing, The US election, The Covid and some insightful news for celebrity and local news. So to start off let's talk what was a bit of an endless nightmare that was the US election. We saw the destruction at the hands of what I would call a giant baby toddler throwing his pacifier out of the pram going off on a tangent about things that don't exist unless in his head and from the likes of everyone who listened to him from the media and all that have strted to cut off his ramblings and have the look on their faces when he goes on for about an hour on complete lies, well at least we will fiinally see the end of him in a few more days.

In other news, the Covid or as I like to call it the Backstreet Boys Reunion because like the virus it comes back alright. This has taken over our lives for the last few months that I am certain that Quarantine Fatigue has really been made affect (I mean I haven't slept properly in about 5 months) but it looks like some good news is that we have some vaccines that could be starting to be distributed by the end of the month, but it should of course not mean that we should jump straight into thinking our lives go back to normal straight away as it will take time for us all to recover, it may take more then one shot and it will have side affects but other then that I am sure that everything will work out just fine but until then keep yourself safe, wash your hands and wear a mask and all that because we don't want you to leave us.

In celebrity news, a big name celebrity has just announced that they are Now identified as Transgender and Non-Binary and that is the star of Juno and Netflix's Umbrella Academy Elliot Page. They released a statement earlier this week on twitter confirming it and I for one respect their decision and that I hope they continue to do great things in their line of work.

That is all I can know for the likes of news that is considered to be good news for the moment but I will try and test the waters for the likes of that information and finding the good bits of news and otherwise I hope that you enjoyed anyway. As always I hope that you enjoy, stay safe out there and good luck on your travels young adventurers

Farewell

Sam H

item.title: The Hobbies and Interests of a Lonely Traveller
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Well hello there fellow travellers. I am not going to be too long on this one as I have already explained the likes of my interested in the about me but I will give a little break down of each of them and why I find them intersting

Video Games: So yes I have a big love and enjoyment for Video Games from the likes of simple jokey fun games, to Deep elaborate Indie Title Phenomeons, to intricate and groundbreaking story driven games, there is something so mesmerising about Video Games that really appeals to me. If I can think of my all time Favourite Games some of them include Super Mario Galaxy 1+2 (just from it's innovative way of playing in a large 3d adventure and it's creativeness), The Last Of Us (as the two games really show the true raw feeling of survival and go beyond the Limits of what a story driven game should be and takes a risk and pays it off and it is a series of games that has me in floods of tears everytime I play through them) Animal Crossing (as sometimes when you can't afford or have the time to get away for a while, going off to the mayor of a small town or island is all the relaxing you need) and so many more that I can't name them all.

Movies and TV: If there is one thing that I have learned to miss but also have some time to catch up on is the likes of Movies and TV shows. I love movies as they are a gateway to other worlds and it is nice to escape for a little while now and again and the same can be said for Tv Show. For some of my favourie Movies include Pixar Films (Especially Toy Story and Monsters Inc), Spider-man Into the Spider-verse, The Most recent Planet of the Apes Trilogy, Logan, the MCU and DCEU, The Dark Kight Trilogy, Ready Player One, Back to the Future and so many more. As for TV show I enjoyed the likes of Game Of Thrones, Steven Universe, Gravity Falls, Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D, The Mandalorian and so many more of them too.

Yoga/ meditation/ walks: these three aspects of exercise have helped me with the likes of reducing stress, keep physically flexible and just as a bit of a calming mechanism for me as if I didn't have them or did them I probably be a sad, broken lonely mess I would be then what I am today.

Music: Now to say that My music tast is different to the common people can be. true as I am not one of the biggest fans of the modern music scene as personally every song and tempo of the song sound too similiar. As for me the Music I love is the likes of the classics from the 60s to the early 2000s , the likes of Soundtracks from Movies, Shows and Games and then my favourite type of genre that has it's place for modern music for me for it's creativity and feeling original everytime is the genre of Indie and Comedy as some of my all time bands are TWRP a group of intergalactic funky space being from beyond the cosmos that resides in Canada, StarBomb a band that has a mix of comedy while working with the likes of video games to create this hilarous gimmick, planet booty for the likes of being the aspect of body positivity and my all time favourite band of Ninja Sex Party which has a superhero and a ninja teaming together to sing about songs on dinosaurs fighting in space with lasers against shark, rovots and aliens, a rock ballad about the journey through space and time to save a princess, a song where they make Math Romantic (yes I am serious), a song about bringing a date home but the home is your parents house and hilarity ensue, a song of being a part of the coolest group around and even a song about how everyone is cool and unique on the inside and that is why I love them so much.

Books and Sleeping: as I said I have wanted to write some books from another page on this topic and now and again I do like to get lost in a good book here and there from adventures and horror, to biographies and romance and comedy, there is something about reading amongst the lines of books that is so peaceful to me. As for sleeping, I don't think I really need to describe that one, do I?

If there are any more content that I can provide for the likes of this I will do just that. But we all have our own levels of favourite Hobbies and Things

item.title: What The Future adventures I have in mind
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Well travellers, it seems that the likes of our travels have brought us the unknown aspects of the future and what it can hold for us all. Today I am going to use the likes of telling some of the aspects on some of the things that I am working on and hope to be achieving in the near future so come along won't you

Cosplay: So one of the big things that I have been wanting to do for quite a while now but haven't had the time to do but want to start evolving more (as some of these costumes and characters I have created for some of these skits and stuff have a very minimal effort to them) is to do cospaly. I have been inspired by a few people I know and from the likes of events past that I have been too and I want to find a time to get to crafting some stuff and all that jazz to create myself into my own unique characters with their deep aspects to the whole situation (some fromm my past like Classy Man Sam, Loose Cannon, Gelactacool) and some of my new ones as well (Such as Detective Locke or Shimmer) and maybe If some fellow colleagues can help me out in some area of that it will hopefully get me flying onto creating something special. with assembly required

Cartoon: So, this one has been brewing in my mind for quite a while now and it is something that I want to create for the course of a little over three years now. Essentially, this animated series in it's simplest terms is about a group of everyday people who are normal awkward people by day but have a collective power passed down from legend tthat grants them this ability to travel into the vast and interconnected realm of the mindscape and are the guardians and sacred protectors of peoples thoughts and dreams from being taken over by Night Caller, the Dark overlord of the Nightmare realm and his vast gallery of creatures and spooky figures that will do anything that can go beyond the mind and control the world. It is essentially a mix between Ghostbuster and Power Rangers meets inception and have the inspiration of the deep storytelling and have a vast array of representation similiar to the likes of Animated Series like Gravity Falls, Steven Universe, Infinity Train, Adventure Time and so much more and I hope that with the right people and the time to get it in motion, it will hopefully be a success

Books: there has always been a fascination to me about writing a book or two and I have the concept of three: The first one which I have done a little bit into is this story of a man who wakes up on this small boat in the middle of nowhere with no sign of land anywhere to be seen, he doesn't remember much and he is covered in cuts and bruises but he must know that he needs to get back to civilisation. Along the way he will come across an island resort that is full of cannibals, some confrontations with some Modern Day Pirates, accompanied by a fellow prisoner, lost and fearful in a triangle of mystery and dangerous creature and haunted by a storm and a giant from the depths below with the added mix of discovering some pieces with a strange symbol to them that may piece the whole beginning of how he ended up on that boat and how he can fix what he did wrong and set things right. It has a mix of heart, emotion, adventure, some humour and scares and all with a deeper meaning to it all by the time you reach the final pages. The Second Book is somewhat of a childrens book about a little tree but I haven't fully fleshed that one out just yet but will have some message of encoragement and about saving the environment. The last book I have is the idea of either being a large book or maybe as a childrens book about this little kid known as Shimmer and the one thing that he doesn't have is to have a dream in life as all of those around them and they want one for themselves and they go to the one thing that could help and that is to wish upon a star. So that night, they pick out the biggest star in the sky and hope to grant their wish but then suddenly all the stars start to fall from the sky and dissappear and the big wishing star starts to float away from Shimmer. So they go off on a journey through vast and colourful lands and meet and help some weird and wonderful creatures and people to discover who or what is causing who is stealing or making all the stars fall and get their wish fulfilled (with the help of a group of intergalactic heroes of course). If I can at least craft together the likes of these stories, it would be very interesting for them to be a reality

Podcast: another Idea was to expand upon the likes of a podcast with starting with the tester pilot as a starting point and have some aspect of bringing some fellow colleagues in as other characetrs or emotions in some method but I will workshop that. I also want to have a seperate podcast option as an idea to really branch out to others in topic of discussion as being more of a chat about anything and not being resorted to just one topic and can be on anything they may want to talk about from one or multiple options of their choosing as being more of a chill or debating like podcast but the idea of getting some peoples to be interested will be the next question

Shop: The last thing I can think about is the likes of creating a shop as being inspired by the likes of some fellow good friends of mine but the concept of what to create and through what form will be the next question. I have some ideas of what to create and give to people to entertain or to brighten up their day (Like Maybe one of those books I was talking about and designing some concepts pieces based on the characters that I have crafted but that will take time) but I hope to do so in the future

Acting: In the likes of in the past I have done my level of acting from the likes of Shorts and Skits from college and social media and I have done the likes of acting before in some stage productions and even in the likes of the big screen production as I have been casted as an extra for a movie that is coming out in 2021 with Matt Damon and Ben Affleck starring in it and it was quite exciting to be learning to fight with weapons and all that exciting stuff. I hope that as time goes on that I will get to really get my acting talents out there by applying for more acting roles in plays, applying for extra roles in films and shows that will hopefully lead to possible bigger roles and I will do the likes of other stuff from creating the likes of more skits and story shorts with my improving skills from acting and editing to make them even better in the near future for social media, work pieces and maybe onto Youtube and stuff likes that.

item.title: Who Inspires me
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
You know, cyber travellers, it can be a question of ask that you wonder on your journey across land and code you ask yourself who is it that inspires me on this long journey. would it be a fair maiden or bard or some particular form of person that you are inspired by on your life travels and do you have any known that you don't? Well I am going to give you some of my own Travellers and people of tales that inspire me from my personality and life travels

Dan Avidan: The First one is from the likes of a tall and handsome man is from the likes of a Man named Dan Avidan. This guy is the lead vocalist and musician of one of my all time favourite bands of Ninja Sex Party. What I appreciate about this man is that he may sing some hilarious and rocking Jams, but he is one of the most wholesome and nicest beings that I know and he gives his effort and his time to give back to the community from weekly charities, music and from spreading positivity whenever he can and he inspires me for being Nice, giving back and for being more interested in music then I was before and I appreciate him for it.

Nolan North: Another one of these Idols is from the realm of being a voice acting Powerhouse and that is Nolan North. Antime I watch an animation or play a game where he is a voice of a character I enjoy the level of performance and his style he brings to the game and he just seems like a really nice guy. I know this as I have a signature and actually met the man himself a few years ago and he was such a really nice dude.

Troy Baker: Another Big inspiration of mine is another Voice Actor and he goes by the name of Troy Baker. Like Nolan, he has had a vast Library of voice work and acting and he is just one of the most chill dudes and I enjoy any work that he give. I also have met the man himself and I have his Signature that is hanging on my wall for over 5 years now and it is a special piece and trinket for me

There are so many other that I know and Love that inspire me from those that inspire me to create through sketch, those that inspire me with the idea of ideas can be interested once they are fleshed out and so many other area but I feel that their is one other person or group that inspire me and that is each and everyone of you that is looking or reading this right now as well as all those I know and Love. I know this may seem a little cliche but I honesty do think that everyone I know from the way that they create, show thei passion, their ethic, personality and everything is something that really enjoy and inspire me from what they show from their work and from those that appreciate whatt I do and how I can help out in anyway that I can and I personally think that everyone has helped me to shape out who I am and what I will be and it is honestly something that I am very proud and I hope from meeting new people and see all of you create and express yourself will give me the same feeling of continuing to create so much more in the future and I really appreciate all that you do and I hope you continue to be excellent and amazing.

item.title: Inspiration wall
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded: My my dear traveller it seem you have been through a lot and that you have seen nothing but sadness and despair but fear not I may have a solution as I will like to welcome you to the Inspiration wall where it is a place of peace, a place of comfort and a place of positivity where you can let all of your sadness, hate and despair drift away and leave you at peace and relaxation for a while and then continue on your journey through the ever growing word, and be at peace when you feel it. (Probably be a place of quotes and a big comment section to leave messages for a wall, make sure any offensive stuff is censored or removed if it is hurtful to some)

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
So, before we get into all of my works and travels and all that more interesting stuff, let me address the elephant in the room and that is who am I exactly, well let me put it to rest. First off my name is that I go by many names but I Go by the name of Sam and I am the simple young age of 20 yet I feel I have the look or someone older and the back that is a few days away from retirement. I come from the likes of the mythical land of Ireland in the city of Dublin where I reside from birth to this very day. So with introductions made let me get down to my favourite things and all sort of things and that is my love.. for media and so much more. I have such a strong spot for the likes of all things Media ever since I was a small child and ever since then that love for it has grown for it ever single day from Film and Animation (which I have a major soft spot for and hope to pursue in the future), photography, Illustrations, sketching and so much more and it is what I am currently in my 3rd year of college doing an intricate course on all things media so I guess it was a lucky instance that I found myself in a course I am well versed in.

Besides the likes of Media I do have the likes of some of my favourite hobbies and all that including the likes of sketching, Listening to Music, Playing Video Games, Watching Movies and TV, Meditation and Yoga, going on Walks, creating fun and interesting skits and all that for social media and myself, creating some new ideas and all that for others and going out of my way to help others from my friends, family, loved ones and everyone else that needs help or just a little pick me up in any way I can and I hope to continue on to make that change in the process in every day that I can. I would continue on but I feel that I will lose you from this point so I will get into some bits of that Later so travel on your Journeys and I will see you in the different areas of this portfolio

item.title: A tale of Music and magic
item.dc:creator: Shimmer Star23
item.content:encoded:
Hello there fellow travellers, come gather I have a tale of old that I came across from reading of my Journals and emails about the story of a night long ago, a night of Music, adventure, Dinosaurs, Funkatronic Robots and creatures from beyond space and time, Superheroes and Ninja and of a night of pure fun and feel good vibes to it all as I tell a tale of old from the time when the world outside the cyberverse was not so different and weird and was actually Normal. So let me not delay and let me get to telling this story

So, in case you don't know but I have a weird taste in music and their is a particular band that is my personal favourite that falls into the Indie Comedy Band genre and that is a Band known as Ninja Sex Party or NSP for short. Anyway I have been a big fan of their work for about their 10 years since they have been a band and I have loved their stuff ever since from their songs that are big budget but look like it was on a small budget look to them, to beautiful animated songs to even really emotional and beautifully made covers of songs from the 60s to 80s with their backing band and another favourite comedy band of mine TWRP and they are also part of another band known as StarBomb.

Anyway back to the topic at hand, it was back in June of last year when they announced for the first time ever that they are having their first European Tour to celebrate their 10 years as a band and their first stop on the tour was in Dublin. When they announced this I will tell no lie I cried with Happiness (which may explain one of the reasons for Why I Cry in general) and I knew that I had to go see them. So the day came when the tickets went on sale and when I obtained one for myself my excitement for it began to grow. Fast forward to Mid October and the day that I have been waiting for finally arrived and my excitement levels were through the roof and nothing could bring it down for that day.

So the night arrived and I made my descent to the event all the way over in Vicar Street at the time for those with the VIP tickets (yes I splashed the cash for it because I deserved it from all other things and hard work that I went through up to that point) and I went in to a special QandA with the two beautiful men themselves of Danny Avidan known as his Alias of Danny Sexbang and Brian Wecht who is known for the talently Dangerous Ninja Brian as well as a signed posted from the two of them. That special Q and A had lots of great things including learning of the feeling they had when they knew that they were big, teaching them in the Irish Linguel and I even got picked by them to ask them a question (which is a true highlight moment and for the question itselfmay be odd but essentially there is an old inside joke that Brian asks Danny to tell himself that "I'm a Sexy Widdle Baby") and getting my question answered and capturing the response on video is a true highlight. Anyway after that Q and A it was when the general audiences began to flood into the place and it was amazing to think that their was so many people from this island that love their work and it felt right. I also met up with some old good friends and talked to some new ones as well while we waited for the show and the special guests to start.

Finally the time came for the show to start and the first to make their appearance was another comedy band that have become another favourite of mine known as Planet Booty that had a different mix of different styles of music (as well as a glorious Disco Ball in the shape of an Ass) and they show that all problems can be solved from the power of Booty, taking off Pants (which they have recently made an alternate version to help stop the spread of Backstreet fever of staying safe and caring for yourself in these scary times) and getting Naked amongst all the other things.Following on from them came the intergalactic group of TWRP that consisted of Drummer Haeve Hogan, Bass Guitarist Commander Meouch, guitarist Captain Phobos and Band leader, Atomic Karate Master and Synth and Keytar player Doctor Sung and they came to sing about having a positive Body Image, how to learn in the Ancient Wisdom of Atomic Karate, learning the ways to Synthesize Her, liking the way you dance with No Pants on and many more hits.

Then finally it was time for the main event to appear and it began with an animated opening to the show that was a planned story for the whole show of an intergalactic Tyranosaurs Rex off to stop the NSP show because he hates Awesomeness. The band of TWRP came back out in the darkness and began to play the bands theme song (what other band or musician do you know has their own theme song?) And through the extreme levels of cheering and the chants of TWRP and NSP they burst out onto the stage with Danny in his amazing Colourful Spandex suit and Cape (which is something that I kind of want to make myself, as their is two different versions of that suit and I kind of want to make both of them.... what I have my own tastes of making some fun things) and his partner in Crime of Ninja Brien who is Fast and deadly, who is known for Stabbing Dudes and Writing Some Tasty Melodies (as well as having a PHD in Particle Physics (this is true)). From there they kicked out their european tour about being part of the coolest group in the world with the Cool Patrol dance (which is one of my anthems in life), we then learn some establish peacekeeping when you bring shame to someone. This leads to think that maybe sometimes you want to wish that you were even more awesome then you already were and that is through the magical capabilities of being a Unicorn Wizard. We took part in a chant of Rock F**k led by Brian the master himself before we took a trip to the past by spinning right round like a record... well after a mix up where Brian starts to play a Bloopy Reggae Jam and got us all to join in and feeling vibey. Then those Science lessons came into practice as we get a slowed down version about the tale of Dinosaurs having a laser fight in Space with Robots and Sharks and Aliens from Mars that ripped solos on their V-neck Guitars. Soon the Tyrannical Tyranosaurs Rex made his presence known to the two heroes and Dan went off to fight his robot Stegosaurus and Dino bot fiends while Brian and TWRP gave him some Jazzy fighting music. We then took things slow and we sung a song about falling in love and how when you do you get a Heart B**er (sidenote before we entered the show there was fans who made the excellent effort of going around and giving us all a small paper heart to put over our phone flashlights and give the band a more romantic mood for the song and it was beautiful and wholesome to see). But then terror as the realm was soon under attack by the armies of the dead underneath the Blood Red son. Luckily they had a secret weapon besides the crowd singing and that was through the might of The Kracken (Yes they had a Kracken and it was amazing). When one threat was dealt with another showed its face as an unknown powerful force was stealing the starlight of the long nights and only a young boy named Strife and a team of Starlightians can get it back with a Jam that is personally one of the best and most beautiful Music Videos of all time and we were all an honorary member of the Starlight Brigade. It was soon confrontation time with the Tyrannical Tyranosaurs and the use of simple instruments on their own wasn't enough to kill him and the only way to kill him was by the power of music and Awesomeness and soon the Villain was slain and the show was saved.

It was then when Dan got personal and said that everything is going to be okay and everything will work out in the end which made me think of why I love these bands so much in the first place. They hold a place in my heart as they helped me see that I shouldn't just hide away my weirdness and quirkiness and that I should embrace it and be who I should be. They also helped me through some really tough times from the past and even in the present day and they shall continue to be and they inspire me to do some great things too. It is then that we learn of the question of going back in Time and telling your Younger self (in this case that Danny's younger self is Finn Wolfhard from Stranger Things) that everything is going to be great and that even when you doubt yourself that you should know that you are cool as F**k on the inside and that you are a star tonight and a Spandex Butterfly for life and that the reason you may feel doubtful is possibly due to you going through an Awkward phase from age 12 to 29 (So I have about another 9 years to go through I guess). This was where the show at first supposedly ended before we had the pleasure of a Double encore that started with the amazing Juggling masterwork of One Ninja Brian and tonend the show with one last song that was sure to be The Hit of that you can save anyone with the power of music. And with that the show was over and I went home with my signed poster, the songs stuck in my head (as they already were for a long time before) my Spandex Butterfly shirt and my Starlight Brigade shirt as well as some great memories.

So that is the story of one of the best night of my life and If they ever come back to Dublin again for another show I would be there no matter what to see them live again with all of their tasty ass Jams and I hope to listen and be inspired by them for many years to come (and hopefully if they ever decide to come to any of these conventions that are usually held throughout the years after the Backstreet Boys Reunion Tour has died down, I would love to meet them one day) and in anytime I know to always rock the F**k on.
